docs.abstract: The Democrat from New York will lead a crucial investigative panel involved in the impeachment inquiry into President Trump.
docs.snippet: The Democrat from New York will lead a crucial investigative panel involved in the impeachment inquiry into President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Democrats elected Representative Carolyn B. Maloney of New York on Wednesday to lead the Oversight and Reform Committee, making her the first woman ever to head the crucial investigative panel at a time when it is helping conduct the impeachment inquiry into President Trump.

headline.main: Carolyn Maloney Elected First Woman to Lead House Oversight Panel
headline.print_headline: Maloney Elected to Lead Oversight Panel

docs.abstract: A veteran diplomat responded in real time to Twitter attacks by President Trump.
docs.snippet: A veteran diplomat responded in real time to Twitter attacks by President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: Marie Yovanovitch was the American ambassador to Ukraine until May, when she was removed by President Trump after a smear campaign orchestrated by Rudy Giuliani, the president’s personal lawyer. In a July 25 phone call with Volodymyr Zelensky, the Ukrainian president, Mr. Trump described Ms. Yovanovitch as “bad news,” adding, “She’s going to go through some things.”

docs.abstract: 2 days of public hearings. How did we get here? Allegations of bribery. And more.
docs.snippet: 2 days of public hearings. How did we get here? Allegations of bribery. And more.
docs.lead_paragraph: Marie L. Yovanovitch, the former ambassador to Ukraine and longtime diplomat, testified on Friday, the second day of public hearings in the impeachment inquiry, about her time in Ukraine. She spoke from decades of diplomatic experience about the situation there and about her removal and the way she was treated by President Trump.

docs.abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said the police and protesters should refrain from violence. Senator Mitch McConnell said President Trump should make forceful statements on Hong Kong.
docs.snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said the police and protesters should refrain from violence. Senator Mitch McConnell said President Trump should make forceful statements on Hong Kong.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Monday called for all sides to exercise restraint in the escalating Hong Kong conflict, and said the territory’s government should start an independent investigation into incidents during the half-year of pro-democracy protests. That inquiry presumably would include reviewing accusations of police misconduct.

headline.main: Pompeo Calls for Restraint in Hong Kong, and McConnell Asks Trump to Speak Up
headline.print_headline: Pompeo Calls for Restraint in Hong Kong as McConnell Prods Trump

docs.abstract: Testimony by Gordon D. Sondland gave Democrats the crisp, accusatory lines they sought. But Republicans elicited an account of one conversation  that they hope will help exonerate President Trump.
docs.snippet: Testimony by Gordon D. Sondland gave Democrats the crisp, accusatory lines they sought. But Republicans elicited an account of one conversation  that they hope will help exonerate President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Gordon D. Sondland had not even finished his testimony on Wednesday before it was being called the “John Dean moment” of the President Trump impeachment drama. With the presidency on the line, a once-trusted lieutenant pointed the finger at Mr. Trump in a proceeding that could lead to Watergate-style charges of high crimes and misdemeanors.

headline.main: In an Echo of Watergate and John Dean, an Adviser Points to Trump

docs.abstract: The lawyer, Robert Luskin, also represented the Republican strategist Karl Rove and likely spared him a perjury charge.
docs.snippet: The lawyer, Robert Luskin, also represented the Republican strategist Karl Rove and likely spared him a perjury charge.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Republican strategist Karl Rove told a federal grand jury conducting a high-profile investigation in 2004 that he had never talked to a journalist who disclosed the identity of an undercover C.I.A. officer. Eight months later, he advised that he had refreshed his recollection: Actually, he had talked to the journalist.

headline.main: Lawyer With Iconoclastic Bent Navigates Sondland Through Testimony Issues
headline.print_headline: Witness’s Oft-Blunt Testimony Aligns With His Uncompromising Lawyer

docs.snippet: John Sullivan, the deputy secretary of state, told lawmakers he believed the president’s personal lawyer was involved in the plot to remove the ambassador to Ukraine.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — John Sullivan, the deputy secretary of state, said on Wednesday that President Trump’s personal lawyer Rudolph W. Giuliani was involved in a smear campaign to oust the ambassador to Ukraine, publicly confirming a key part of the saga behind the impeachment inquiry.
